        </ul>
        <ul class='gallery-dot-list'>
          <li class='gallery-dot-item'><button class='gallery-dot js-gallery-dot current'></button></li>
          <li class='gallery-dot-item'><button class='gallery-dot js-gallery-dot'></button></li>
        </ul>
        <ul class='gallery-btns'>
          <li>
            <button class='gallery-btn-prev js-gallery-prev icon ion-ios-arrow-left'></button>
          </li>
          <li>
            <button class='gallery-btn-next js-gallery-next icon ion-ios-arrow-right'></button>
          </li>
        </ul> 
      </section>

      <h6>Demo</h6>
      <section class='video-responsive'>
        <iframe class='iframe' src='https://player.vimeo.com/video/183410426' width='420' height='315' frameBorder='0' allowFullScreen></iframe>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section class='wrapper project-conclusion'>
      <h3>Thoughts</h3>
      <p>
        I enjoyed making this project I found it
        interesting to work with canvas and javascript
        to make something easily playable on most browsers.
        Overall I would have liked to made the enemy sprites
        rounder like a circle inside of a rectangle so it would
        be easier to click on them. If I were to continue working
        on it I would add new levels so that you feel like you progress
        beyond the tutorial without just having the free for all level.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>
